ffmpegfs is an open source fuse based read only
transcoding file system.It converts various
video and audio formats on the fly and supports
many formats.

By default only root has access to this filesystem
for other users, uncomment user_allow_other in
/etc/fuse.conf

Example:

ffmpegs --desttype=mp4 input_dir output_dir -o allow_other,rw

It is licensed under GPLv3
